{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013iQm2Xw2huo5KjCojpuU4A","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.UUID;\n     4→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.ArticleFavoritesCount;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleById;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n     8→\n     9→@AllArgsConstructor\n    10→public class ArticleFavoritesCountImpl implements ArticleFavoritesCount {\n    11→\n    12→  private final FindArticleById findArticleById;\n    13→  private final FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    14→\n    15→  @Override\n    16→  public long handle(UUID articleId) {\n    17→    final var article = findArticleById.handle(articleId);\n    18→    return favoriteRelationshipRepository.favoritesCount(article);\n    19→  }\n    20→}\n    21→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012wasVMvXM1hNbSfEKhMNvo","session_id":"dc68c8b7-f26e-40c7-b046-67d783731ba6","uuid":"504b0694-d82a-467d-b2e1-bfeb95e2cbf8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01E7cTFyYJwBu6fgudXoNRDv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.UUID;\n     4→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateSlugByTitle;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleRepository;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.SlugProvider;\n     8→\n     9→@AllArgsConstructor\n    10→public class CreateSlugByTitleImpl implements CreateSlugByTitle {\n    11→\n    12→  private final ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    13→  private final SlugProvider slugProvider;\n    14→\n    15→  @Override\n    16→  public String handle(String title) {\n    17→    String slug = slugProvider.slugify(title);\n    18→    if (articleRepository.existsBySlug(slug)) {\n    19→      slug += UUID.randomUUID().toString();\n    20→    }\n    21→    return slug;\n    22→  }\n    23→}\n    24→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012wasVMvXM1hNbSfEKhMNvo","session_id":"dc68c8b7-f26e-40c7-b046-67d783731ba6","uuid":"129194ed-713e-42f4-9699-b3088064f6eb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XVPR8GSjuzs9v2v9Qnp7Xq","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     4→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateComment;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleBySlug;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentBuilder;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.NewCommentInput;\n    11→\n    12→@AllArgsConstructor\n    13→public class CreateCommentImpl implements CreateComment {\n    14→\n    15→  private final CommentRepository commentRepository;\n    16→  private final FindUserById findUserById;\n    17→  private final FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    18→  private final CommentBuilder commentBuilder;\n    19→\n    20→  @Override\n    21→  public Comment handle(NewCommentInput newCommentInput) {\n    22→    final var author = findUserById.handle(newCommentInput.getAuthorId());\n    23→    final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(newCommentInput.getArticleSlug());\n    24→    final var comment = commentBuilder.build(author, article, newCommentInput.getBody());\n    25→    commentRepository.save(comment);\n    26→    return comment;\n    27→  }\n    28→}\n    29→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012wasVMvXM1hNbSfEKhMNvo","session_id":