{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UUyfP6yDAef28wKxQbtQgW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleBySlug;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindCommentsByArticleSlug;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\n     9→\n    10→@AllArgsConstructor\n    11→public class FindCommentsByArticleSlugImpl implements FindCommentsByArticleSlug {\n    12→\n    13→  private final FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    14→  private final CommentRepository commentRepository;\n    15→\n    16→  @Override\n    17→  public List<Comment> handle(String slug) {\n    18→    final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(slug);\n    19→    return commentRepository.findCommentsByArticle(article);\n    20→  }\n    21→}\n    22→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012wasVMvXM1hNbSfEKhMNvo","session_id":"dc68c8b7-f26e-40c7-b046-67d783731ba6","uuid":"005bd2cb-5672-4d38-8400-85304d96577e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Lk2HNo1kcpTY8UoxAsheEp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     4→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindMostRecentArticlesByFilter;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleFilter;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleRepository;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.PageResult;\n     9→\n    10→@AllArgsConstructor\n    11→public class FindMostRecentArticlesByFilterImpl implements FindMostRecentArticlesByFilter {\n    12→\n    13→  private final ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    14→\n    15→  @Override\n    16→  public PageResult<Article> handle(ArticleFilter articleFilter) {\n    17→    return articleRepository.findMostRecentArticlesByFilter(articleFilter);\n    18→  }\n    19→}\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012wasVMvXM1hNbSfEKhMNvo","session_id":"dc68c8b7-f26e-40c7-b046-67d783731ba6","uuid":"b91f107e-993c-4ebe-8216-40479253da1f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015qRknTMGvs23U7e58sgkyR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.LinkedList;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     6→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateTag;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagRepository;\n    11→\n    12→@AllArgsConstructor\n    13→public class FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExistsImpl implements FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists {\n    14→\n    15→  private final TagRepository tagRepository;\n    16→  private final CreateTag createTag;\n    17→\n    18→  @Override\n    19→  public List<Tag> handle(List<String> names) {\n    20→    final var tags = tagRepository.findByNames(names);\n    21→    tags.addAll(createTags(nonexistent(tags, names)));\n    22→    return tags;\n    23→  }\n    24→\n    25→  private List<Tag> createTags(List<String> names) {\n    26→    final var tags = new LinkedList<Tag>();\n    27→    names.forEach(name -> tags.add(createTag.handle(name)));\n    28→    return tags;\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  private List<String> nonexistent(List<Tag> existing, List<String> allNames) {\n    32→    return allNames.stream()\n    33→        .filter(name -> existing.stream().noneMatch(tag -> tag.getName().equalsIgnoreCase(name)))\n    34→        .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    35→  }\n    36→}\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012wasVMvXM1hNbSfEKhMNvo","session_id":"dc68c8b7-f26e-40c7-b046-67d783731ba6","uuid":"d3effbb3-b853-40da-9c61-79587dc1b066"}
