{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GabgY9TRrrEuJRAw6dr5cy","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolation;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.Validator;\n     5→import java.util.Set;\n     6→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     7→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.ModelValidationException;\n     9→\n    10→@AllArgsConstructor\n    11→public class ModelValidator {\n    12→\n    13→  private final Validator validator;\n    14→\n    15→  public <T> T validate(T model) {\n    16→    Set<ConstraintViolation<T>> constraintViolations = validator.validate(model);\n    17→\n    18→    if (!constraintViolations.isEmpty()) {\n    19→      final var messages =\n    20→          constraintViolations.stream()\n    21→              .map(ConstraintViolation::getMessage)\n    22→              .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    23→      throw new ModelValidationException(messages);\n    24→    }\n    25→\n    26→    return model;\n    27→  }\n    28→}\n    29→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SJtD3wLsYGvAd833rHyiXD","session_id":"dc68c8b7-f26e-40c7-b046-67d783731ba6","uuid":"e83bfde7-8faf-4e6a-a373-48dae8cb7624"}
