{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016aavAXo9u8ZZCPyFy2fCio","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/utils/ResourceUtils.java has been updated. Here's the result of running `cat -n` on a snippet of the edited file:\n     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.utils;\n     2→\n     3→import java.security.Principal;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import java.util.UUID;\n     6→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.*;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.*;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.PageResult;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n    12→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n    13→\n    14→@Component\n    15→public class ResourceUtils {\n    16→\n    17→    private static final int DEFAULT_LIMIT = 20;\n    18→    private final FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername;\n    19→    private final IsFollowingUser isFollowingUser;\n    20→    private final FindArticleTags findArticleTags;\n    21→    private final IsArticleFavorited isArticleFavorited;\n    22→    private final ArticleFavoritesCount articleFavoritesCount;\n    23→\n    24→    public ResourceUtils(FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername,\n    25→                         IsFollowingUser isFollowingUser,\n    26→                         FindArticleTags findArticleTags,\n    27→                         IsArticleFavorited isArticleFavorited,\n    28→                         ArticleFavoritesCount articleFavoritesCount) {\n    29→        this.findUserByUsername = findUserByUsername;\n    30→        this.isFollowingUser = isFollowingUser;\n    31→        this.findArticleTags = findArticleTags;\n    32→        this.isArticleFavorited = isArticleFavorited;\n    33→        this.articleFavoritesCount = articleFavoritesCount;\n    34→    }\n    35→\n    36→    public ProfileResponse profileResponse(String username, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    37→        final var user = findUserByUsername.handle(username);\n    38→        final var profileResponse = new ProfileResponse(user);\n    39→        if (loggedUserId != null) {\n    40→            profileResponse.setFollowing(isFollowingUser.handle(loggedUserId, user.getId()));\n    41→        }\n    42→        return profileResponse;\n    43→    }\n    44→\n    45→    public ArticleResponse articleResponse(Article article, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    46→        final var author = article.getAuthor();\n    47→        final var profileResponse = profileResponse(author.getUsername(), author.getId());\n    48→        final var tags = findArticleTags.handle(article);\n    49→        final var favoritesCount = articleFavoritesCount.handle(article.getId());\n    50→        final var articleResponse = new ArticleResponse(article, profileResponse, favoritesCount, tags);\n    51→        if (loggedUserId != null) {\n    52→            articleResponse.setFavorited(isArticleFavorited.handle(article, loggedUserId));\n    53→        }\n    54→        return articleResponse;\n    55→    }\n    56→\n    57→    public ArticlesResponse articlesResponse(PageResult<Article> pageResult, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    58→        final var resultResponse =\n    59→                pageResult.getResult().stream()\n    60→                        .map(article -> articleResponse(article, loggedUserId))\n    61→                        .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    62→        return new ArticlesResponse(resultResponse, pageResult.getTotal());\n    63→    }\n    64→\n    65→    public CommentResponse commentResponse(Comment comment, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    66→        final var commentAuthor = comment.getAuthor();\n    67→        final var authorResponse = profileResponse(commentAuthor.getUsername(), loggedUserId);\n    68→        return new CommentResponse(comment, authorResponse);\n    69→    }\n    70→\n    71→    public UUID getLoggedUserId(Principal principal) {\n    72→        return principal != null ? UUID.fromString(principal.getName()) : null;\n    73→    }\n    74→\n    75→    public CommentsResponse commentsResponse(List<Comment> comments, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    76→        final var resultResponse =\n    77→                comments.stream()\n    78→                        .map(comment -> commentResponse(comment, loggedUserId))\n    79→                        .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    80→        return new CommentsResponse(resultResponse);\n    81→    }\n    82→\n    83→    public int getLimit(int limit) {\n    84→        return limit > 0 ? limit : DEFAULT_LIMIT;\n    85→    }\n    86→}\n    87→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019dgv6Zr4tY62fLHA7Nznz9","session_id":"dc68c8b7-f26e-40c7-b046-67d783731ba6","uuid":"060a5108-547c-4dca-9853-19ecb4f50ede"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019dgv6Zr4tY62fLHA7Nznz9","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have successfully converted all 6 REST controller files from JAX-RS (Quarkus) to Spring MVC (Spring Boot). Here's a summary of the conversions I completed:\n\n## Files Written\n\nAll 6 files have been successfully converted and written to the Spring Boot project:\n\n### 1. **ArticlesResource.java**\n- **Location**: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ArticlesResource.java`\n- Converted JAX-RS annotations to Spring MVC\n- Changed from `@Path(\"/articles\")` to `@RestController` + `@RequestMapping(\"/articles\")`\n- Replaced JAX-RS annotations: `@GET` → `@GetMapping`, `@POST` → `@PostMapping`, `@PUT` → `@PutMapping`, `@DELETE` → `@DeleteMapping`\n- Changed `@QueryParam` → `@RequestParam`, `@PathParam` → `@PathVariable`\n- Replaced `@Context SecurityContext` with `Principal`\n- Changed `Response` to `ResponseEntity`\n- Replaced `@NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper` qualifier with `@Qualifier(\"noWrapRootValueObjectMapper\")`\n- Removed `@RolesAllowed` and `@PermitAll` (security handled by Spring Security configuration)\n\n### 2. **UsersResource.java**\n- **Location**: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UsersResource.java`\n- Converted to Spring MVC with `@RestController` and `@RequestMapping`\n- Changed `Response` to `ResponseEntity<UserResponse>`\n- Replaced Quarkus `UnauthorizedException` with Spring's `BadCredentialsException`\n- Used constructor injection (removed `@Inject` and `@AllArgsConstructor`)\n\n### 3. **UserResource.java**\n- **Location**: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UserResource.java`\n- Converted to Spring MVC controllers\n- Changed `@Context SecurityContext` to `Principal`\n- Extracts user ID from `Principal.getName()` instead of `SecurityContext.getUserPrincipal().getName()`\n\n### 4. **ProfilesResource.java**\n- **Location**: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ProfilesResource.java`\n- Converted to Spring MVC\n- All JAX-RS annotations replaced with Spring equivalents\n- Security context replaced with Principal\n\n### 5. **TagsResource.java**\n- **Location**: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/TagsResource.java`\n- Simple conversion to Spring MVC\n- ObjectMapper injection uses `@Qualifier` annotation\n\n### 6. **ResourceUtils.java**\n- **Location**: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/utils/ResourceUtils.java`\n- Changed from `@ApplicationScoped` to `@Component`\n- Updated `getLoggedUserId()` method to accept `Principal` instead of `SecurityContext`\n- Constructor injection (removed Lombok `@AllArgsConstructor`)\n\n## Key Conversion Changes\n\n1. **Annotations Mapping**:\n   - `@Path` → `@RequestMapping`\n   - `@GET` → `@GetMapping`\n   - `@POST` → `@PostMapping`\n   - `@PUT` → `@PutMapping`\n   - `@DELETE` → `@DeleteMapping`\n   - `@QueryParam` → `@RequestParam`\n   - `@PathParam` → `@PathVariable`\n   - `@Consumes`/`@Produces` → `consumes`/`produces` attributes in mapping annotations\n\n2. **Dependency Injection**:\n   - Removed Lombok `@AllArgsConstructor`\n   - Explicit constructor-based injection\n   - `@ApplicationScoped` → `@Component` / `@RestController`\n\n3. **Security Context**:\n   - `@Context SecurityContext` → `Principal` parameter\n   - `securityContext.getUserPrincipal()` → direct `principal` usage\n\n4. **Response Types**:\n   - JAX-RS `Response` → Spring `ResponseEntity`\n   - `Response.Status.OK` → `ResponseEntity.ok()`\n   - `Response.Status.CREATED` → `ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CREATED)`\n\nAll files have been successfully migrated from Quarkus JAX-RS to Spring Boot MVC!"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dc68c8b7-f26e-40c7-b046-67d783731ba6","uuid":"66086ae9-df3e-44e7-ab11-d6d4e1eb0026"}
