{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01AnC9Q4TY9RCdfcMcQy8yry","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.security.ForbiddenException;\n     4→import io.quarkus.security.UnauthorizedException;\n     5→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.ErrorResponse;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.*;\n     8→import org.jboss.resteasy.reactive.server.ServerExceptionMapper;\n     9→\n    10→public class ExceptionMappers {\n    11→\n    12→  @ServerExceptionMapper\n    13→  public Response unauthorized(UnauthorizedException e) {\n    14→    return Response.ok(errorResponse(\"Unauthorized\"))\n    15→        .status(Response.Status.UNAUTHORIZED.getStatusCode())\n    16→        .build();\n    17→  }\n    18→\n    19→  @ServerExceptionMapper\n    20→  public Response forbidden(ForbiddenException e) {\n    21→    return Response.ok(errorResponse(\"Forbidden\"))\n    22→        .status(Response.Status.FORBIDDEN.getStatusCode())\n    23→        .build();\n    24→  }\n    25→\n    26→  @ServerExceptionMapper\n    27→  public Response emailAlreadyExists(EmailAlreadyExistsException e) {\n    28→    return Response.ok(errorResponse(e)).status(Response.Status.CONFLICT.getStatusCode()).build();\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  @ServerExceptionMapper\n    32→  public Response usernameAlreadyExists(UsernameAlreadyExistsException e) {\n    33→    return Response.ok(errorResponse(e)).status(Response.Status.CONFLICT.getStatusCode()).build();\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  @ServerExceptionMapper\n    37→  public Response userNotfound(UserNotFoundException e) {\n    38→    return Response.ok(errorResponse(e)).status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND.getStatusCode()).build();\n    39→  }\n    40→\n    41→  @ServerExceptionMapper\n    42→  public Response invalidPassword(InvalidPasswordException e) {\n    43→    return Response.ok(errorResponse(e))\n    44→        .status(Response.Status.UNAUTHORIZED.getStatusCode())\n    45→        .build();\n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  @ServerExceptionMapper\n    49→  public Response tagNotFound(TagNotFoundException e) {\n    50→    return Response.ok(errorResponse(e)).status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND.getStatusCode()).build();\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  @ServerExceptionMapper\n    54→  public Response articleNotFound(ArticleNotFoundException e) {\n    55→    return Response.ok(errorResponse(e)).status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND.getStatusCode()).build();\n    56→  }\n    57→\n    58→  @ServerExceptionMapper\n    59→  public Response modelValidation(ModelValidationException e) {\n    60→    return Response.ok(errorResponse(e)).status(422).build();\n    61→  }\n    62→\n    63→  private ErrorResponse errorResponse(String e) {\n    64→    return new ErrorResponse(e);\n    65→  }\n    66→\n    67→  private ErrorResponse errorResponse(RuntimeException e) {\n    68→    return new ErrorResponse(e.getMessage());\n    69→  }\n    70→}\n    71→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WuPJyEz9UcHLwWhQ8qhiyW","session_id":"dc68c8b7-f26e-40c7-b046-67d783731ba6","uuid":"6717e805-8446-4bef-98ae-788462941f2c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GPd4BaG1vtxvkGF5doo3XX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolationException;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n     5→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.ExceptionMapper;\n     6→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.Provider;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.ErrorResponse;\n     8→\n     9→@Provider\n    10→public class BeanValidationExceptionMapper\n    11→    implements ExceptionMapper<ConstraintViolationException> {\n    12→\n    13→  @Override\n    14→  public Response toResponse(ConstraintViolationException e) {\n    15→\n    16→    ErrorResponse errorResponse = new ErrorResponse();\n    17→\n    18→    e.getConstraintViolations()\n    19→        .iterator()\n    20→        .forEachRemaining(constraint -> errorResponse.getBody().add(constraint.getMessage()));\n    21→\n    22→    return Response.ok(errorResponse).status(422).build();\n    23→  }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WuPJyEz9UcHLwWhQ8qhiyW","session_id":"dc68c8b7-f26e-40c7-b046-67d783731ba6","uuid":"e5c860be-c794-4b65-8986-055b7d8a226a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015ePHNmjcy5aURTkrT81fDh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleModelBuilder;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentBuilder;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagBuilder;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserModelBuilder;\n    14→\n    15→@ApplicationScoped\n    16→@AllArgsConstructor\n    17→public class EntityUtils {\n    18→  private final UserModelBuilder userBuilder;\n    19→  private final TagBuilder tagBuilder;\n    20→  private final ArticleModelBuilder articleBuilder;\n    21→  private final CommentBuilder commentBuilder;\n    22→\n    23→  public User user(UserEntity userEntity) {\n    24→    final var id = userEntity.getId();\n    25→    final var username = userEntity.getUsername();\n    26→    final var bio = userEntity.getBio();\n    27→    final var image = userEntity.getImage();\n    28→    final var password = userEntity.getPassword();\n    29→    final var email = userEntity.getEmail();\n    30→    return userBuilder.build(id, username, bio, image, password, email);\n    31→  }\n    32→\n    33→  public Tag tag(TagEntity tagEntity) {\n    34→    return tagBuilder.build(tagEntity.getId(), tagEntity.getName());\n    35→  }\n    36→\n    37→  public Tag tag(TagRelationshipEntity tagRelationshipEntity) {\n    38→    return tag(tagRelationshipEntity.getPrimaryKey().getTag());\n    39→  }\n    40→\n    41→  public Article article(ArticleEntity articleEntity) {\n    42→    return articleBuilder.build(\n    43→        articleEntity.getId(),\n    44→        articleEntity.getSlug(),\n    45→        articleEntity.getTitle(),\n    46→        articleEntity.getDescription(),\n    47→        articleEntity.getBody(),\n    48→        articleEntity.getCreatedAt(),\n    49→        articleEntity.getUpdatedAt(),\n    50→        user(articleEntity.getAuthor()));\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  public Comment comment(CommentEntity commentEntity) {\n    54→    return commentBuilder.build(\n    55→        commentEntity.getId(),\n    56→        user(commentEntity.getAuthor()),\n    57→        article(commentEntity.getArticle()),\n    58→        commentEntity.getBody(),\n    59→        commentEntity.getCreatedAt(),\n    60→        commentEntity.getUpdatedAt());\n    61→  }\n    62→\n    63→  public FavoriteRelationship favoriteRelationship(\n    64→      FavoriteRelationshipEntity favoriteRelationshipEntity) {\n    65→    return new FavoriteRelationship(\n    66→        user(favoriteRelationshipEntity.getUser()),\n    67→        article(favoriteRelationshipEntity.getArticle()));\n    68→  }\n    69→}\n    70→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WuPJyEz9UcHLwWhQ8qhiyW","session_id":"dc68c8b7-f26e-40c7-b046-67d783731ba6","uuid":"eadd3cb2-ab03-4e01-9b71-0e1c11f780a2"}
