{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011mtowQPU2k8JfgxC4WpgMd","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n     4→import java.util.UUID;\n     5→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator.ModelValidator;\n     7→\n     8→@Named\n     9→@AllArgsConstructor\n    10→public class UserModelBuilder {\n    11→  private final ModelValidator modelValidator;\n    12→\n    13→  public User build(String username, String email, String password) {\n    14→    return modelValidator.validate(\n    15→        new User(UUID.randomUUID(), username, email, password, null, null));\n    16→  }\n    17→\n    18→  public User build(\n    19→      UUID id, String username, String bio, String image, String password, String email) {\n    20→    return modelValidator.validate(new User(id, username, email, password, bio, image));\n    21→  }\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dc68c8b7-f26e-40c7-b046-67d783731ba6","uuid":"993d6d14-11c0-48bd-95f0-dc47d3a46467"}
